  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Daewon Temple
  author: Park Chun-ryeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Three years lost in ledgers and documents, illness haunting my weary frame.
    Retired at last, I seek out old friends and cherished bonds.
    Through dense trees climbing high and low, the path seems to vanish—
    yet flowers bloom in succession, unveiling a spring all their own.

    The gorge's shadows shift with sun and cloud, different with each glance,
    while mist and haze paint purple and jade anew with each dawn and dusk.
    Remote Huiyuan needs no crossing of streams—
    for mountain-dwellers welcome and bid farewell to wanderers such as I.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Huiyuan (慧遠) refers to the famous Buddhist monk Huiyuan, alluding to the spiritual sanctuary and hospitality of the temple
